        <prompt>What was the primary purpose of the Chinese Exclusion Act of 1882?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">To prohibit Chinese laborers from immigrating to the United States</option>
            <option letter="b">To regulate Chinese business ownership</option>
            <option letter="c">To protect Chinese immigrants</option>
            <option letter="d">To promote trade with China</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Chinese Exclusion Act was the first major law restricting immigration to the United States, specifically targeting Chinese laborers and reflecting growing anti-Chinese sentiment in the West.</explanation>
