    <question>
        <prompt>What was the significance of the Comstock Lode discovery?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It was the largest silver deposit in America and sparked Nevada's population growth</option>
            <option letter="b">It produced mainly gold</option>
            <option letter="c">It had minimal economic impact</option>
            <option letter="d">It was quickly exhausted</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Comstock Lode discovery in 1859 was the richest silver deposit in American history, leading to Nevada's rapid development and statehood, while also advancing mining technology.</explanation>
