    <question>
        <prompt>How did the development of refrigerated rail cars change the meatpacking industry?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It allowed fresh meat to be shipped long distances and centralized meat processing in Chicago</option>
            <option letter="b">It only impacted local markets</option>
            <option letter="c">It decreased meat consumption</option>
            <option letter="d">It raised meat prices significantly</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Refrigerated rail cars revolutionized the meat industry by allowing fresh meat to be shipped long distances, leading to the centralization of meatpacking in Chicago and transforming American food distribution.</explanation>
